SASS Installation Steps

1. Linux Installation (Optional):
   - Open Ubuntu terminal
   - Install Node Version Manager (nvm) version 0.39.7:
     $ curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
   - Exit the terminal using the exit command
   - Reopen the terminal
   - Install Node.js version 20.16 using nvm:
     $ nvm install 20.16
     $ nvm use 20.16

2. Installation Anywhere (Optional):
   - Ensure Node.js is installed on your system
   - Install SASS version 3.7.4 globally using npm:
     $ npm install sass -g
   - Or install SASS version 3.7.4 locally in your project:
     $ npm install sass@3.7.4

3. Verify Installation:
   - Check SASS version:
     $ sass --version
   - Should output: 3.7.4 (or similar version)

4. Alternative Installation Methods:
   - Using yarn: $ yarn global add sass@3.7.4
   - Using pnpm: $ pnpm add -g sass@3.7.4
   - Download from official website: https://sass-lang.com/install

Note: The installation steps may vary depending on your operating system and package manager preferences.
